add0e001-73c9-5509-8a06-70c3abd783b7,tg:rubgr:843,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Ad [Addendum] 16. Bruegel: Way to Calvary. Jan van AMSTEL. Entry of Christ into Jerusalem, Stuttgart; Procession to Calvary, Louvre. Both in arrangement of figures very near to Bruegel's Calvary. Less to the Calvary in the Vienna Academy. In the Louvre Procession there is the city on the left, the place of execution on the right. column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] 16. Bruegel: Way to Calvary. Jan van AMSTEL. Entry of Christ into Jerusalem, Stuttgart; Procession to Calvary, Louvre. Both in arrangement of figures very near to Bruegel's Calvary. Less to the Calvary in the Vienna Academy. In the Louvre Procession there is the city on the left, the place of execution on the right. Christ quite small with cross, and there are even 'Tümpel' auch - reflections in the wak figures (dogs) in right foreground. But there is not the large group of the holy mourners - which is in Massys' picture.</content>
